  "prompt": "Will I get refund after preparation of chart for wait listed ticket?",
  "response": "The refund policy for waitlisted train tickets varies depending on the railway operator and their specific terms and conditions. Here\u2019s what generally happens in most cases:\n\n1. **Preparation of Chart**: If your ticket is still waitlisted after the preparation of the final chart (usually 4 hours before departure), the ticket will not be confirmed, and the amount paid for the ticket will be **automatically refunded** by the railway operator.\n\n2. **Cancellation Before Chart Preparation**: If you choose to cancel your waitlisted ticket **before the preparation of the chart**, you can typically get a refund after deducting applicable cancellation charges. The specific charges depend on how close to the departure date the cancellation is made.\n\n3. **Confirmation of Ticket**: If your waitlisted ticket gets confirmed before or after the preparation of the chart, it will no longer be eligible for a refund unless you cancel it according to the standard cancellation rules.\n\n4. **Partial Payment (Tatkal Waitlist)**: For Tatkal waitlisted tickets, a **100% refund** is provided if the ticket remains waitlisted after the preparation of the chart, as Tatkal tickets are charged at a higher rate.\n\nAlways check the **refund status** on the official website or app of the railway operator to confirm the refund process. Refunds are usually credited back to the original payment method within a few working days.",
